arts.ttl: Republic of Ireland v Portugal, France v Ukraine, and more: World Cup 2026 qualifying – live
arts.sum: ⚽ World Cup qualifying updates, 7.45pm GMT kick-offs ⚽ Live scores | England v Serbia – live | Email Luke This was Ed’s take on Group I. Norway are now six points clear of Italy … Norway lead Italy by three points and no one else can finish in the top two. A win for Norway at home to Estonia on Thursday would in effect secure qualification before they travel to San Siro on Sunday because the astonishing 29 goals plundered by Erling Haaland and co from six matches have given the team a frankly ridiculous goal difference of +26, 16 ahead of Italy. Gennaro Gattuso’s side need maximum points from their games, which start in Moldova on Thursday, and a Norway slip against Estonia to avoid the playoff for which they appear destined as they try to qualify for a first World Cup since 2014.
